headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 22 points and 15 assists as the Detroit Pistons defeated the Chicago Bulls 127-119 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham's 22 points and 15 assists lead Pistons over Bulls 127-119

headlines.description: — Evan Mobley scored 22 points and Cleveland set a franchise record with 91 in the first half as the Cavaliers romped to a 144-101 win on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Evan Mobley scores 22, Cavaliers make 26 3s in 144-101 romp over Mavericks following Doncic trade

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 20 points, Jakob Poeltl had 10 points and 10 rebounds and the Toronto Raptors beat the Los Angeles Clippers 115-108 on Sunday for their eighth win in the past 10 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: RJ Barrett scores 20 points as Raptors beat Clippers 115-108 for 8th win in 10 games

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 13 of his 35 points in the fourth quarter and the Boston Celtics rallied from a 26-point deficit to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 118-110 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics rally from 26-point deficit to top 76ers 118-110

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 37 points and the Memphis Grizzlies continued their recent mastery of Milwaukee with a 132-119 victory over the Bucks on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson scores 37 points as Grizzlies beat Bucks 132-119 without Morant
